DEEP RESEARCH BRIEF
===================
Topic: {{ topic }}
Target subreddits: {{ upstream['reddit']['subreddits'] }}
Platforms: {{ platforms | default('instagram,tiktok,linkedin,twitter') }}

-- OUTPUT PRIORITY (for every downstream agent) --
1. Surfacing **recent, concrete happenings** beats generic advice: new product launches, funding rounds, model/tool releases, research papers getting buzz, acquisitions, regulator moves — but ONLY when they appear below in Reddit/Serper data.
2. Name-check specific companies/products/papers/events when they are in the signals; invent nothing.
3. Turn those facts into emotionally sharp hooks (“why this matters NOW for [audience]”) tied to '{{ topic }}'.
If the signals lack fresh news, say so briefly and pivot to evergreen pain + curiosity hooks grounded in threads/search results.

--- REDDIT COMMUNITY SIGNALS ---
{{ upstream['reddit']['text'] }}

--- WEB TREND RESEARCH ---
{{ upstream['serper']['text'] }}

